  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from \"Hartley Coleridge: A Reassessment of His Life and Work\" by A. Keanie (Springer, 2008), p. 2: \"The following letter from STC [Samuel Taylor Coleridge] to his friend, the tanner and philanthropist, Thomas Poole (1765–1837), outlines some of the details of Hartley's birth, and reveals the typical first-time father's proud and shell-shocked reaction: 'On Tuesday Morning I was surprised by a Letter from Mr Maurice, our medical attendant, informing me that Mrs Coleridge was delivered on Monday, September 19th, 1796, halfpast two in the Morning, of a SON—& that both she and the Child were uncommonly well...'\"\\n",
